Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.15,0:00:03.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just as flowing water has no form,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.02,0:00:04.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the breeze is invisible,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.82,0:00:06.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,deductions take all shapes and styles\Nin each and every case to be solved.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.29,0:00:08.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The case where a detective is the victim
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.39,0:00:10.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shin-ichi solves the case sharply
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.39,0:00:12.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He sees through the one and only truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.12,0:00:14.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A child in appearance with the I.Q. of\Nan adult, no case is left unsolved
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.13,0:00:16.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,when Detective Conan\Ncomes to the scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.56,0:01:59.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We come to this villa on an overnight trip
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.57,0:02:01.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,& meet Kazuyoshi Sunaoka
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.97,0:02:04.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,who plays a famous detective
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.24,0:02:06.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,in the popular TV series "Urban Hunter"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.11,0:02:08.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,& other staff members\Nworking on the series
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.64,0:02:09.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.71,0:02:11.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,behind the scenes of the show
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.31,0:02:14.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,relations between these people\Nare very hostile...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.25,0:02:22.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and then with a single gunshot
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.52,0:02:25.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mr. Sunaoka is killed\Nby an unknown assailant!!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.66,0:02:29.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,after firing from the rocks\Nacross the valley
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.46,0:02:31.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the killer climbed down the rope
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.33,0:02:32.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,& used a boat to escape,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.07,0:02:34.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that's what was believed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.80,0:02:38.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It takes 30 minutes to get\Nto the other side
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.34,0:02:43.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so no one from the villa could have\Npossibly committed the crime!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.74,0:02:47.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the killer is one of those 3
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.41,0:02:50.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know I'm right!!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.29,0:03:01.79,Dialogue,Sign,0,0,0,,{\pos(342.563,393.143)}MURDER OF THE FAMOUS DETECTIVE\NPART 2
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.50,0:03:07.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, Mr. Sunaoka's killer
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.23,0:03:10.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I believe, went down to the stream\N& escaped.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.30,0:03:13.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've just issued an all points bulletion\N& we are searching
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.77,0:03:16.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but I must ask all of you once more
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.84,0:03:20.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to go over the details of what happened
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.98,0:03:23.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the morning,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.25,0:03:26.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was in Mr. Tahara's room\Ngoing over the scenarios....
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.09,0:03:29.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Then in the afternoon, I went to the\Nhunting in the woods with Mr. Sunaoka,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.59,0:03:32.49,Dialogue,Sign,0,0,0,,{\pos(351.371,364)}Atsuaki Nagatsuka\NProducer
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.39,0:03:31.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\an8}we got back at about 6:30
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.56,0:03:33.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\an8}then joined everyone for dinner\Nright after that
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.33,0:03:36.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\an8}After talking with Mr. Nagatsuka,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.46,0:03:39.97,Dialogue,Sign,0,0,0,,{\pos(346.967,357.143)}Toshiaki Tahara\NScenario Writer
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.00,0:03:39.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\an8}I stayed in my room\Nuntil the evening writing...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.07,0:03:43.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Mr. Sunaoka called me to his room\Nin the morning
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.60,0:03:45.84,Dialogue,Sign,0,0,0,,{\pos(343.192,332.571)}Noe Tanigawa\NSunaoka's manager
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.07,0:03:45.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,& he told me about switching agencies....
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.07,0:03:47.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,we had a little argument....
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.67,0:03:49.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see...an argument you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.94,0:03:51.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y, yes....
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.08,0:03:54.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was on the archery grounds\Nin the afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.21,0:03:56.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I ran into Mr. Mouri & his family there...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.92,0:03:58.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I got back here after 6
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.75,0:04:00.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then joined the others
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.89,0:04:01.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uh huh....
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.35,0:04:05.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Me? I was busy working, of course...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.23,0:04:11.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\an8}I'm alone today so I was very busy,\NI don't remember all the details though...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.23,0:04:11.70,Dialogue,Sign,0,0,0,,{\pos(345.08,364)}Yusaku Akashi\NSansou's Innkeeper
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.13,0:04:13.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hmm...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.97,0:04:17.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come on, it's your bedtime Conan
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.30,0:04:20.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, but I want to listen a little more....
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.84,0:04:23.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No! Dad'll scold you again
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.34,0:04:25.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know., but it's too early for bed....
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.71,0:04:29.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure dad'll be at it all night
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.45,0:04:32.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'd better not get in his way\Nso just go to sleep
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.38,0:04:36.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh alright...\NI'll go to sleep so you can go now
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.76,0:04:40.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way, I'm staying right here\Nuntil you're asleep
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.93,0:04:45.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Alright then, now for after dinner
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.03,0:04:51.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was about 7:50 when Mr. Sunaoka\Nleft the restaurant with Ms. Tanigawa
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.74,0:04:56.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right after that, Mr. Tahara went to\Nthe kitchen to get more drinks
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.98,0:05:01.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At 8 sharp, Mr. Nagatsuka got a call from\Nthe station and went to the front desk...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.28,0:05:07.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and right after that,\NI got a call from Mr. Sunaoka
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.45,0:05:11.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he abruptly ended the conversation &\Nthat's when we heard the gunshot
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.76,0:05:14.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ms. Tanigawa, who had been\Ntaking a shower came out to the veranda
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.39,0:05:18.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and discovered the bullet hole\Nin Mr. Sunaoka's window
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.20,0:05:21.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We went to get Mr. Akashi\Nat the front desk &
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.20,0:05:23.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,got the master key to unlock the door
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.84,0:05:27.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At 8:05, we discovered the body
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.54,0:05:35.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means Mr. Sunaoka was killed\Nbetween 8 & 8:05....
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.95,0:05:38.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,.....Conan?...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.42,0:05:46.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hah....\Nhe fell asleep unusually fast tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.26,0:05:51.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Good night....
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.21,0:06:04.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Phew, I thought she'd never leave
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.42,0:06:16.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd like to go over in more detail what you\Nwere all doing before & after the murder
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.42,0:06:20.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why bother, you know it was\Nsomebody from the outside, don't you...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.63,0:06:24.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, we still must clarify\Nwhat the victim was doing
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.06,0:06:28.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mr. Sunaoka was alone\Nin his room locked from the inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.67,0:06:30.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How would we know what he was doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.07,0:06:32.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes well....that is true....
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.34,0:06:35.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We don't even have time to mourn him!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.94,0:06:37.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Give us a break!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.61,0:06:39.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me for saying this
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.71,0:06:43.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but it seems you 3 had\Nsome bad feelings toward Mr. Sunaoka
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.08,0:06:45.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.75,0:06:49.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you implying 1 of us killed him?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.55,0:06:52.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not really,\Nthis is all part of the investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.16,0:06:58.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mr. Sunaoka seemed very picky about\Nthe scenarios, isn't that right, Mr. Tahara?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.76,0:07:04.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Lately, the viewers solve the crime\Nbefore I do. That won't do
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.84,0:07:08.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mr. Sunaoka, put yourself in my shoes,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.01,0:07:10.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have to write scenarios\Nto fit YOUR personality
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.44,0:07:13.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was only being honest
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.65,0:07:16.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And as for you,\NMr. Nagatsuka the producer...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.35,0:07:22.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know all about it. I hear you're\Npocketing some of the production fees
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.06,0:07:26.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How dare you! That's a lie!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.69,0:07:29.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It, it really was a lie!!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.49,0:07:31.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, an investigation will clear that up
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.96,0:07:34.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uh, why, of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.43,0:07:36.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now for Ms. Tanigawa,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.20,0:07:40.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mr. Sunaoka talked about\Nswitching agencies, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.41,0:07:45.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm the biggest star your agency's got,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.68,0:07:48.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,if you lose me, you probably won't\Nbe able to stay in the business, huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.68,0:07:51.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well Mr. Detective, I'll catch you later
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.02,0:08:00.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On top of that, you're the only one\Nwithout a witness to verify your alibi
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.79,0:08:01.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How can you say that!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.79,0:08:05.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You all saw me in my room\Nfrom the garden restaurant, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.66,0:08:09.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, but it was AFTER the gunshot...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.90,0:08:16.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,another thing, the rest of you also had\Nan opportunity to contact the shooter
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.78,0:08:20.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is crazy!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.71,0:08:23.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But then you can\Nnever tell about Ms. Tanigawa!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.05,0:08:25.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean by that!?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.75,0:08:28.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't lover boy dump you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.12,0:08:31.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mr. Nagatsuka!!\NDon't be ridiculous!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.22,0:08:34.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now now everybody just calm down
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.33,0:08:38.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Yokomizo!\NThe findings regarding the rifle are back!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.96,0:08:39.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.57,0:08:44.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The rifle was one of those kept\Nin the hunting management office,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.64,0:08:46.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the rope also came from there!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.77,0:08:50.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The markings on the bullet taken\Nfrom the victim & the ones from the rifle
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.11,0:08:51.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,were a perfect match...!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.48,0:08:55.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,ho!? And what is this!?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.35,0:08:59.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A hole was opened in bottom of the bullet\N& the tip's been sharpened.....
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.72,0:09:02.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was the purpose for this...?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.95,0:09:05.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...It certainly doesn't make sense does it
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.32,0:09:09.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's spiral grooves inside the hole...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.86,0:09:11.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's like a screw
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.06,0:09:13.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Co, Conan.....
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.17,0:09:16.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why you, you're supposed to be sleeping!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.07,0:09:20.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I got up because I was so thirsty...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.47,0:09:23.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Alright already,\Ngo get some water & then go back to bed!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.61,0:09:24.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.71,0:09:26.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, I almost forgot!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.38,0:09:27.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Uncle Kogoro
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.11,0:09:30.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, what is it now?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.25,0:09:33.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What did Mr. Sunaoka say\Non the telephone?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.55,0:09:35.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,THAT is none of your business
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.59,0:09:40.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aw but those were the last words of\NMr. Sunaoka the big star weren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.89,0:09:43.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, so you're one of those low brows?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.53,0:09:48.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He asked me to come to his room\Nto talk detective talk!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.33,0:09:55.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But then he said "Hey what's that" &\Nseemed surprised & hung up
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.71,0:09:57.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I knew it...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.54,0:10:00.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since the rifle markings match,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.98,0:10:04.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it means what I found mixed in\Nwith the pieces of glass...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.32,0:10:06.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where'd it come from.....
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.49,0:10:10.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which one?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.53,0:10:15.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it's so heavy
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.63,0:10:22.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I knew it! Just as I thought.....
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.17,0:10:24.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes! Now I know\Nhow the trick was worked!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.07,0:10:29.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this mark on the floor.....
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.41,0:10:34.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I concentrated so hard on the pieces\Nof glass I didn't notice it before...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.68,0:10:37.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be......
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.49,0:10:44.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I knew it....there's one here too!\Nwhich means......
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.79,0:10:48.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The real weapon\Nshould be behind this door....
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.76,0:10:55.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And! The person staying in that room\Nis also the killer!!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.21,0:11:05.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The rifle markings matched,\Nyou don't need us here anymore, do you
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.11,0:11:06.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hah.....
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.75,0:11:08.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me officer
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.48,0:11:11.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.78,0:11:13.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have something to tell you
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.99,0:11:19.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh? Room 304?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.03,0:11:23.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sh, Detective Yokomizo said\Nto do a secret search,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.90,0:11:25.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,here's the master key
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.23,0:11:27.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hurry, OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.30,0:11:28.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, sure.....
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.04,0:11:33.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then we'll be going back\Nto our rooms now
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.21,0:11:35.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh alright!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.31,0:11:38.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shall we continue this\Nat 8 tomorrow morning then?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.31,0:11:40.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's so early!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.78,0:11:42.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I guess it's OK
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.52,0:11:45.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you for your time
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.32,0:11:47.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mr. Mouri, why don't you get some rest
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.59,0:11:52.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're going to go join\Nthe search downstream, excuse us
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.63,0:11:55.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,....Good luck...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.40,0:12:06.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait just a minute!!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.77,0:12:13.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You three over there... and\NDetective Yokomizo, hear me out first
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.38,0:12:18.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aha!! That's the pose!!\NSo it's hit you, didn't it!!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.62,0:12:20.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, it finally hit me
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.79,0:12:25.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, but it doesn't seem like\Na job for “Sleeping Kogoro" this time...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.22,0:12:27.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're wrong about that. After all,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.33,0:12:32.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The killer is one of those three!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.03,0:12:34.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What!!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.57,0:12:35.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was that!!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.94,0:12:38.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I understand, Mr. Mouri!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.87,0:12:42.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Alright you 3, why don't you\Nhave a seat on the sofa once more?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.44,0:12:48.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the first,\Nit appeared to be an obvious case
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.58,0:12:51.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,where the murderer was someone\Nfrom the outside....
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.38,0:12:55.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why did the murderer\Nleave the rifle behind?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.42,0:13:00.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The murderer could have tossed it into\Nthe stream or hidden it in the woods
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.33,0:13:03.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Another thing, both the rifle & the rope
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.63,0:13:08.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the murderer used\Nto get down to the stream,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.00,0:13:10.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,why were these things wet by the rain?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.80,0:13:13.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes! It rained in the evening!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.41,0:13:17.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The rifle was left about 8pm,\Nit shouldn't be wet, it is strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.28,0:13:26.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason for that is, both the rifle &\Nrope were planted there BEFORE the rain
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.35,0:13:31.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In fact, it was dry\Nunder some parts of the rifle
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.82,0:13:37.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That proves the rifle was left there\Nbefore it rained in the evening
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.93,0:13:42.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,....which means the rifle was\Nwhat actually the murder weapon
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.33,0:13:46.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the markings matched, didn't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.77,0:13:48.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before I explain that,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.01,0:13:52.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,why do you suppose the murderer\Nwent through all that trouble?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.11,0:13:57.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Making it appear like\Nhe was shot from across valley......
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.65,0:14:01.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if the murderer was an outsider,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.42,0:14:05.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,all the murderer had to do was prove\Nhe or she never came close to the villa
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.06,0:14:12.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was absolutely no reason\Nto plant fake evidence
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.83,0:14:17.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The murderer is someone\Nwho needed an alibi,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.57,0:14:20.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that's why the scene had to be\Nacross the valley....
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.67,0:14:24.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,....That's right\N...the murderer is one of you three!!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.28,0:14:30.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ho, hold on just a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.92,0:14:35.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're not magicians, how did we\Nshoot him without using the rifle!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.95,0:14:39.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right! You haven't been\Nmaking any sense at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.06,0:14:45.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And now I'll go into the details of\Nhow Mr.Sunaoka was actually killed
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.00,0:14:47.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is ridiculous
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.10,0:14:51.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First, the killer takes the master key from\Nthe front desk when no one is around
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.87,0:14:55.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and sneaks into\NMr. Sunaoka's room on the 3rd floor
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.21,0:14:59.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then props up\Nthe mattress against the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.25,0:15:01.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mattress?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.71,0:15:04.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's a mattress got\Nto do with anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.62,0:15:10.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The killer then went to the hunting ground\Nmanagement office & stole the rifle & rope
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.42,0:15:12.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then the killer went to\Nthe rocky area across the valley &
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.22,0:15:16.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,shot at the window\Nin Mr. Sunaoka's room
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.93,0:15:22.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The killer then left the rifle there &\Ntied the rope to the tree
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.50,0:15:24.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and made it look like\Nthe escape was by water
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.07,0:15:28.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The killer then snuck back\Ninto Mr.Sunaoka's room &
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.97,0:15:34.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,removed the bullet shot into the mattress.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.48,0:15:36.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After replacing the mattress,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.88,0:15:39.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the killer removed\Nall the broken pieces of glass &
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.32,0:15:41.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,hid the hole by drawing the curtains
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.99,0:15:44.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Yokomizo!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.59,0:15:48.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The bullet removed from the body\Nhad some work done to it, didn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.96,0:15:49.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.33,0:15:52.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The killer went back to\Nhis or her own room
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.46,0:15:55.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,& dug a hole into the end of the bullet\Nwhich the killer took out of the mattress
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.83,0:15:58.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tools were used to drill the screw threads
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.54,0:16:01.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,& the tip was sharpened with a file
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.41,0:16:07.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then something the killer had prepared\Nearlier, was screwed into the bullet
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.45,0:16:13.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And now we have a new deadly weapon\Nwith the same markings as the rifle!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.12,0:16:18.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After the preparations had been made,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.82,0:16:21.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the killer went to\Nthe garden restaurant for dinner
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.63,0:16:23.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,when Mr. Sunaoka went back to his room
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.60,0:16:27.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the killer made up some sort of excuse &\Ngot into his room
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.07,0:16:29.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And pierced Mr. Sunaoka
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.10,0:16:34.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,in the forehead, from the front!!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.51,0:16:35.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Pierced!?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.81,0:16:38.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you saying\Nthe weapon was a knife or arrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.71,0:16:39.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An arrow!?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.08,0:16:43.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After killing Mr. Sunaoka,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.55,0:16:47.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the killer moved the body to make it\Nlook like the shot came from the window
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.05,0:16:48.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,& opened the curtains
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.82,0:16:51.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then rescattered\Nthe pieces of glass around
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.79,0:16:55.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,& removed the tip of the arrow\Nfrom Mr. Sunaoka's forehead
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.36,0:16:58.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then left without a snag
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.30,0:17:10.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why Mr. Mouri, you should\Nbecome a scenario writer!!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.78,0:17:12.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was a brilliant story!!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.84,0:17:16.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I don't have the talent\Nto become a writer.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.75,0:17:21.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All the evidence the killer left behind\Nshowed me the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.42,0:17:23.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm just the messenger
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.59,0:17:27.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For instance, along with\Nthe pieces of glass from the window,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.66,0:17:29.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I found some coconut fibers
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.56,0:17:33.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They were from the mattress.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.56,0:17:36.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It probably fell out\Nwhen the bullet was dug out
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.97,0:17:41.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The killer didn't notice them &\Ngathered them up along with the glass
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.44,0:17:43.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see!!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.04,0:17:47.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After that, the killer hid the real weapon
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.55,0:17:50.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,& then went to another location\Nso as not to under suspicion
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.28,0:17:53.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,& called me on my cellular...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.19,0:17:56.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The killer probably saw the number
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.09,0:17:58.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,on the business card\NI handed out during dinner
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.36,0:18:04.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mr. Mouri, you yourself said\Nthe caller was Mr. Sunaoka...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.83,0:18:07.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the phone, Mr. Sunaoka said
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.73,0:18:11.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"How about it? Why don't you come up\Nto my room & we'll talk detective"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.04,0:18:14.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then "Huh?\NHold on a second, what is that?"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.41,0:18:19.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well people,\Ndoes that sound familiar to anyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.24,0:18:23.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's it. That's the dialogue\Nhe said on tonight's show!!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.62,0:18:25.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.88,0:18:27.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, I'm positive!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.69,0:18:31.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I taped it, why don't you see for yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.79,0:18:32.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, I'll do that
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.03,0:18:38.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was the opening scene\Nbut please fast forward it
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.27,0:18:42.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.90,0:18:46.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How about it? Why don't you come up\Nto my room & we'll talk detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.24,0:18:49.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? Hold on for a second, what is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.38,0:18:55.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see...\Nthe killer recorded this line previously
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.68,0:18:58.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,& played it back to\NMr. Mouri on the phone, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.65,0:19:02.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then Mr. Sunaoka was already dead\Nwhen the call was made?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.39,0:19:05.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes...he was already killed...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.06,0:19:08.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only one without\Nan alibi for that time is...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.16,0:19:09.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Yokomizo!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.13,0:19:14.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As you ordered, I searched room 304\N& look at what I found!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.37,0:19:16.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's a bowgun!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.04,0:19:18.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I found an arrow with blood on it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.24,0:19:21.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So this is the murder weapon!?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.71,0:19:23.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And there are screw threads\Non the arrow head
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.58,0:19:27.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mr. Mouri! It's exactly like you said!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.68,0:19:31.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure the killer intended\Nto take them home & destroy them
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.75,0:19:36.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,O, Officer, did you just say room #304?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.22,0:19:37.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean....
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.29,0:19:42.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right...\Nthe killer was staying in room 304
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.66,0:19:45.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Toshiaki Tahara, it's you!!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.80,0:19:49.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't believe it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.54,0:19:53.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mr. Tahara, a little past 7:50,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.87,0:19:55.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you left the room saying\Nyou were going to get more drinks
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.31,0:19:59.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but you went to Mr.Sunaoka's room\N& killed him
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.28,0:20:03.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About 8, you came back looking\Nas if nothing happened
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.38,0:20:06.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You deliberately sat far away
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.55,0:20:09.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so you call me without being seen
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.25,0:20:11.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then you threw something,\Npossibly a firecracker into the valley
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.72,0:20:14.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to make us think a shot was fired
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.90,0:20:20.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Some detective you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.03,0:20:24.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just because\Nthe murder weapon was in my room
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.70,0:20:26.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,doesn't mean it belongs to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.34,0:20:30.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm being set up by the real killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.84,0:20:34.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately for you, I have more proof
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.05,0:20:35.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.18,0:20:37.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's your shoes
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.55,0:20:45.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You see the scratches on the floor?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.72,0:20:48.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me,\Nwould you mind taking your shoes off?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.49,0:20:52.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's pieces of glass stuck in the sole!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.10,0:20:57.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could they be from the pieces\Nscattered around the body?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.84,0:21:01.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure no one else besides us\Nwent near the body
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.54,0:21:07.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So how could be these pieces of glass\Nget under your shoes....
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.15,0:21:10.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were so preoccupied with\Nwhat you had to do,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.38,0:21:16.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you didn't realize you had stepped\Non them. You were too caught up
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.56,0:21:20.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,....You win...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.42,0:21:22.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mr. Tahara!!\NWhy did you do such a thing!?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.39,0:21:27.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Humph! He was also criticizing &\Nmaking fun of the scenarios I wrote,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.06,0:21:29.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,if the ratings were bad, he blamed me...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.77,0:21:32.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I couldn't forgive that Sunaoka for that!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.47,0:21:37.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wanted to show everyone,\Nthe producers, the actors & the police
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.71,0:21:44.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,yes, & I even the most famous detective\Nthat I could commit the perfect crime...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.85,0:21:51.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the victim, of course Bannai\NKujirao Sunaoka was the only choice...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.78,0:23:26.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How about the lead in our next series!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.62,0:23:28.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The title is\N[Kogoro the Famous Detective]!!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.72,0:23:29.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Will you do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.69,0:23:33.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The ratings are guaranteed to be high,\Nyou'll be a famous star in no time!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.99,0:23:36.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That does sound good
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.43,0:23:42.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's get going!!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.17,0:23:42.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.57,0:23:45.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,M, Mr. Mouri......
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.00,0:23:48.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran, we'll want you too....!!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.67,0:23:52.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mr. Mouri!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.94,0:23:55.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I want a chance to be a star!!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.35,0:24:03.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was that sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.16,0:24:12.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's been shot in the forehead!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.56,0:24:15.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You saw a bluish-white flash of light?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.27,0:24:18.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bluish-white light
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.87,0:24:20.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,what could it have been...?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.64,0:24:22.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.94,0:24:28.85,Dialogue,Sign,0,0,0,,{\pos(345.709,296)}A MYSTERIOUS GUNSHOT\NECHOES IN THE DARKNESS
